Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the top from the @butternut squash{1}(no need to peel) then halve lengthways and scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 2cm lengths, then chop into 2cm chunks. Peel the @red onion{1}(peeled) then chop into six wedges. Pop the squash and onion on a large #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and sprinkle over the @ground cumin{2%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Tear the @ciabatta bread{1} into roughly 2cm croutons. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1}, then chop into wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, lime zest, half the lime juice, half the coriander and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

About 10 mins before the veggies are cooked, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and once hot add the @chorizo{60%g} and torn ciabatta croutons. Cook, stirring occasionally until both ingredients have crisped up, taking care not to burn the chorizo, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Once the veggies are done, switch off the oven and remove the tray. Scatter the @baby spinach{125%g} over the squash and onions and return to the now switched off oven for ~{1-2%minutes}, while you get ready to serve.

> The spinach will quickly wilt in the heat of the oven!

In a #large bowl{}, toss together the chorizo, ciabatta croutons, remaining coriander, veggies and spinach. Divide between plates then top with the dressing and remaining lime wedges (on the edge). Dig in!